<subSubSection id="15D00C8BFF86FF90FCEDFCE2FE1A2646" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="193" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D755F00FF86FF91FCEDFCE2FB352551" blockId="2.[826,1429,825,1949]" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">
Remarks — Bertrand (1990) recognised four labidostommatid genera: the Holarctic 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FAA3FC87FC1A20C9" authority="Berlese, 1911" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1911" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" genus="Eunicolina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FAA3FC87FA53202A" box="[1312,1429,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Eunicolina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FCB9FCA4FC1A20C9" author="Berlese, A." box="[826,988,895,919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="429 - 435" refId="ref2862" refString="Berlese, A. 1911 - Acarorum secies novae quindecim - Redia, 7: 429 - 435." type="journal article" year="1911">Berlese, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
characterized by multiplication of pustules and 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FC69FC79FAEA20E4" authority="Robaux, 1977" authorityName="Robaux" authorityYear="1977" box="[1002,1324,930,954]" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" genus="Akrostomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FC69FC79FBB520E4" box="[1002,1139,930,954]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Akrostomma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FB01FC79FAEA20E4" author="Robaux P." box="[1154,1324,930,954]" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="442 - 461" refId="ref3614" refString="Robaux P. 1977 - Observations sur quelques Actinedida (= Prostigmates) du sol d'AmOrique du Nord. VI. Sur deux especes nouvelles de Labidostommidae (Acari) - Acarologia, 18: 442 - 461." type="journal article" year="1977">Robaux, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with a dense reticulate cuticular pattern and characteristized by body shape and cheliceral morphology, the southern hemisphere 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FBFDFBD7FC162719" authority="Feider and Vasiliu, 1969" authorityName="Feider and Vasiliu" authorityYear="1969" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" genus="Sellnickiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actinedida" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FBFDFBD7FB39277A" box="[1150,1279,1036,1060]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Sellnickiella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FA8DFBD7FC162719" author="Feider Z. &amp; Vasiliu N." pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="202 - 207" refId="ref3236" refString="Feider Z., Vasiliu N. 1969 - ROvision critique de la famille des Nicoletiellidae - Proc. 2 nd Int. Congress Acarology: Sutton Bonington, England 1967. Acad. Kiado, Budapest: 202 - 207." type="book chapter" year="1969">Feider and Vasiliu, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
- see also Bertrand (1997) - with loss of the gland-like organ, and the world-wide distributed 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FC27FBAEFBF927D3" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1879" box="[932,1087,1141,1165]" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" genus="Labidostomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FC27FBAEFBF927D3" box="[932,1087,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Labidostomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter was considered ’primitive’ because of the retention of the main (plesiomorphic) characters shared by other representatives of the family, e.g. a primitive famulus, eyes, a pair of gland-like organs, chelicerae not modified; although some species acquired specialized characters that are considered as adaptations (neotaxy of gland-like organs, eye reduction, development of genual of PI, neotrichy, etc). For further taxonomic accounts of modern 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FBA5FA6BFB072696" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1879" box="[1062,1217,1456,1480]" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" genus="Labidostomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FBA5FA6BFB072696" box="[1062,1217,1456,1480]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Labidostomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see, e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FAAEFA6BFC4526B2" author="Bertrand M." pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="27 - 38" refId="ref2881" refString="Bertrand M. 1981 - Nouvelles especes de Labidostomidae de Corse. IntOrOEt biogOographique - Acarologia 23: 27 - 38." type="journal article" year="1981">Bertrand (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FC0EFA08FB1726B2" author="Bertrand M. &amp; Theron P. D." box="[909,1233,1491,1516]" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="247 - 257" refId="ref3037" refString="Bertrand M., Theron P. D. 1990 - Nouveaux Labidostomidae d'Afrique Australe: le genre Labidostoma Kramer 1879 - Acarologia, 31: 247 - 257." type="journal article" year="1990">Bertrand and Theron (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FB58FA08FA5326B2" author="Iavorschi V." box="[1243,1429,1491,1516]" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="47 - 51" refId="ref3308" refString="Iavorschi V. 1992 - Labidostoma motasi n. sp. (Nicoletiellidae) a new species of the mite of Romania - Trav. de l'Instit. de SpOleol. &quot; Emile Racovitza &quot;, Bucharest., 31: 47 - 51." type="journal article" year="1992">Iavorschi (1992)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FCD9FA2DFB282551" author="Bertrand M. &amp; Corpuz Raros L. A." box="[858,1262,1526,1551]" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="361 - 368" refId="ref2986" refString="Bertrand M., Corpuz Raros L. A. 1997 - DiversitO du genre Labidostoma Kramer: nouvelles donnOes apportOes par l'Otude de Labidostoma (Labidostoma) guadalupense n. sp. des Philippines (Acari, Actinedida, Labidostomatidae) - Acarologia, 38: 361 - 368." type="journal article" year="1997">Bertrand and Corpuz Raros (1997)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D755F00FF86FF90FCE3F9FDFE1A2646" blockId="2.[826,1429,825,1949]" lastBlockId="3.[159,762,1139,1304]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="193" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">
Note on the family and genus nomenclature: Etymology of the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FB2FF992FA81253F" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1879" box="[1196,1351,1609,1633]" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" genus="Labidostomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FB2FF992FA81253F" box="[1196,1351,1609,1633]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Labidostomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to both Latin and Greek with 
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FB2CF9B7FAC725DA" box="[1199,1281,1644,1668]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Labidos</emphasis>
referring to the large chelicerae and 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FBF2F954FB7325F8" authorityName="Hadding" authorityYear="1919" box="[1137,1205,1679,1702]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polychaeta (awaiting allocation)" genus="Stoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polychaeta (awaiting allocation)" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FBF2F954FB7325F8" box="[1137,1205,1679,1702]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Stoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FB48F94BFAEF25F9" box="[1227,1321,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">stomatos</emphasis>
, mouth. Berlese, Oudemans, Grandjean, and others selected the orthography with a single ’m’ — which is etymologically correct — whereas other authors imposed an erroneous orthograph (see e.g. the large mandibles of 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FC5EF8E5FAEC2409" authority="Chevrolat, 1837" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" box="[989,1322,1854,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Labidostomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF86FF91FC5EF8E5FBAC2408" box="[989,1130,1854,1878]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="192">Labidostomis</emphasis>
Chevrolat, 1837
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FAB8F8E4FA562409" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1339,1424,1855,1879]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="class">Insecta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF86FF91FCB9F8BAFC362427" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[826,1008,1889,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysomelidae</taxonomicName>
)). Returning to the original generic description of 
<bibRefCitation id="395B22F1FF86FF91FC62F85EFB4F24C3" author="Kramer P." box="[993,1161,1925,1949]" pageId="2" pageNumber="192" pagination="13 - 16" refId="ref3391" refString="Kramer P. 1879 - Neue Acariden - Arch Naturgesch., 45: 13 - 16." type="journal article" year="1879">Kramer (1879)</bibRefCitation>
, we are forced to retain his initial orthographic mistake, i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF87FF90FDD4FBA8FD3427D5" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1879" box="[599,754,1139,1163]" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" genus="Labidostomma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Acari" pageId="3" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FBE8312FF87FF90FDD4FBA8FD3427D5" box="[599,754,1139,1163]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="193">Labidostomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and treat 
<taxonomicName id="9ACA2483FF87FF90FE95FB4DFDC427F0" authorityName="Oudemans" authorityYear="1904" box="[278,514,1174,1198]" class="Arachnida" family="Labidostommatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Labidostommatidae</taxonomicName>
(with a double ’m’) as the valid family name. Note that this does not apply to the more recently established higher taxon (cohort) Labidostomatides.
</paragraph>
